EXTRACTED VALUE: "Did I hurt you?" Her voice was worried, and when Minias shook his head, relief spilled over her, quickly turning to depression.
"He has cut off its lips to make it snarl at us. But we are not made fearful by such things. We are not frightened children."
Gabe sat up straighter. "You're not serious about this."
Inside, the air was warm and dry, pleasant after the bitter cold. I smelled tea and mothballs and years of fried food.
Now I was becoming exasperated. For my fourth attempt, I resorted to fear and threat. "Unless you share, you will be in real trouble!"
"Who are the evictors?" he mumbled, to no one in particular, and he waited a couple of minutes before saying it again.
I looked up to find him staring at me, his forehead slightly furrowed, eyes intent.
